REDIS

Redis sotres data in key-value. Redis stores data in RAM (memory), not primarily on disk.
MongoDB	                                       Redis
show dbs	                                   INFO keyspace
use db	                                       SELECT db
show collections (like tables)	               KEYS *
find()	                                       GET / HGET / LRANGE

If you are in a redis server and if you wan to connect to redis
redis-cli
You’ll get prompt like:
127.0.0.1:6379>
✔ That means you are connected to Redis
🔐 If password is enabled
redis-cli -a <password>
Example:
redis-cli -a RoboShop@1
