sudo dnf install redis -y when we run this only that server become redis server right. to install client also the same command have to use?
❗ First, clear the misunderstanding
sudo dnf install redis -y

👉 This installs the Redis package, which includes:

Redis server (redis-server)
Redis client (redis-cli)
🧠 Important point

👉 Installing Redis package ≠ making it a Redis server

A server becomes a Redis server only when you start the service
🔍 What actually makes it a Redis server?
sudo systemctl start redis
sudo systemctl enable redis

👉 Now it is acting as a Redis server
✅ If you ONLY want client (best practice)
On another server (client machine):

You can still run:

sudo dnf install redis -y

👉 Then:

Don’t start the service ❌
Just use:
redis-cli
